Overview

This lab demonstrates how to use Azure Management Groups to organize subscriptions, implement Role-Based Access Control (RBAC), create custom roles, and monitor activities using Azure Activity Logs.
The objective of this lab was to understand Azure governance and access management best practices in a real-world administrative scenario.

Lab Objectives

Create and manage Azure Management Groups
Organize subscriptions logically
Assign RBAC permissions using Azure AD groups
Configure built-in and custom roles
Understand RBAC inheritance
Monitor administrative actions using Activity Logs
Perform resource cleanup after completion

Technologies Used

Microsoft Azure
Azure Management Groups
Azure RBAC
Azure Activity Logs
JSON Role Definitions
Azure Portal


| Resource                         | Purpose                               |
| -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Management Group                 | Logical organization of subscriptions |
| HelpDesk Group                   | RBAC assignment target                |
| Virtual Machine Contributor Role | VM management permissions             |
| Custom RBAC Role                 | Customized access control             |
| Activity Logs                    | Monitoring and auditing               |


